gomodel:SYNGO_266  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: knock-out of synaptopodin affects synaptic transmission.\nFig. 4: Reduced hippocampal LTP Field excitatory postsynaptic potentials (fEPSP) measured in the CA1 stratum radiatum were evoked by stimulation of the Schaffer collateral commissural afferents in KO animals.\n\n14/3/2017 Pim\n- The postsynaptic element of the annotation comes from the exclusive localization of SYNPO at the postsynaptic spine apparatus. Interfering with SYNPO expression is therefore inferred to regulate synaptic transmission via a postsynaptic mechanism (also spine apparatus is missing here).. Experimental description: Wild-type (male; n 5) and mutant mice (male; n 5) were deeply anesthetized with an overdose of Nembutal (300 mgkg body weight) (p. 10494)..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2017-09-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_266" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

